        "content": "We have the main.cpp fixed, but there might still be issues. Let me verify the current state and check if there are any missing pieces. Also, we need to ensure the platformio.ini has necessary libraries. Let me read platformio.ini and verify dependencies, then check for compilation issues.\n\nAlso, the Display constructor takes no pins but the GxEPD2 template requires display parameters. The current code uses defaults defined in Display.h. That's fine.\n\nHowever, I noticed that the Display class uses GxEPD2_213_BN which is for black/white. The WeActStudio 2.13\" e-ink display is typically the GDEY0213B74 or similar, but GxEPD2_213_BN should work. We might want to use GxEPD2_213_B74 or GxEPD2_213_BN depending on the exact panel. But for now, it's a reasonable choice.\n\nNow I need to ensure the project can compile. Let me check if there are any missing headers or library conflicts.\n\nLet me also verify the platformio.ini has all required lib_deps: GxEPD2, ESPAsyncWebServer, AsyncTCP, ArduinoJson.\n\nLet's also consider that ESPAsyncWebServer might need to be from the PlatformIO library registry. Check if the correct names are used.\n\nI'll read platformio.ini to confirm.\n\nAfter that, we need to verify the complete project structure is correct for PlatformIO. Also, we should provide a README with instructions.\n\nBut before doing all that, let's do a quick review of all files for obvious errors. Let me read key files again.",
