        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "We have a working codebase now. Let me verify all files are consistent and there are no obvious compilation issues.\n\nChecks:\n1. main.cpp includes headers correctly.\n2. Display::showStatus takes (float, int, bool, const char*), main.cpp calls display.showStatus(lastMoisture, lastRaw, calibrating, lastWifiStatus.c_str()).\n3. Sensor::setCalibration takes (int, int) - good.\n4. WebServer.cpp now syncs calibration to sensor.\n5. Display uses GxEPD2_213_BN - need to verify that model exists in GxEPD2 library. For WeActStudio 2.13\", the model is GxEPD2_213_BN. That is correct.\n6. SPI pins for ESP32-S3: typically CS=10, DC=9, RST=8, BUSY=7, MOSI=11, SCK=12. But note that e-ink display may be connected to HSPI or VSPI. On ESP32-S3, the default SPI (VSPI) pins are: MOSI=11, MISO=13, SCK=12, SS=10. User might need to adjust. We should add comments in platformio.ini or a config header. But it's fine for now.\n\nPotential issues:\n- The WebServer uses `DynamicJsonDocument` - deprecated in ArduinoJson 7. Should use `JsonDocument` with static allocation. But for simplicity keep as is; user can adjust.\n- The platformio.ini board is `esp32-s3-devkitc-1` but the user has \"esp32-s3 wroom-1\". The board should be changed to `esp32-s3-devkitc-1` is a generic board. The user may need to set `board_build.mcu = esp32s3` and `board_build.f_cpu = 240000000L`. For now generic is okay.\n- Need to add `board_build.arduino.memory_type = qio_opi`? Not necessary for simple sketch.\n\nMissing: The user asked for \"возможность откалибровать датчик влажности\" - calibration via web server is implemented (POST endpoints). But also need a way to calibrate directly on device without web server? Maybe via serial? The main.cpp currently has serial toggle for calibration mode. That's okay.\n\nAlso missing: The WiFi configuration page is minimal. Could add a status page. But the task was \"написал приложение для esp32 которое бы оценивало влажность по датчику влажности в горшке.